  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Heat a <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pork loin steak[s]</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until beginning to brown</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing with the side of a knife and discard the skin</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>BBQ sauce</strong> and <strong>tomato paste</strong> in a small bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>BBQ glaze</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix</strong> to a large bowl with your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and mix it all together – this is your <strong>slaw</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, remove the pork from the dish and set aside on a clean plate</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to the dish with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>crushed garlic</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, give everything a good mix up and place the dish in the oven for an initial 20 min – these are your <strong>smoky potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 20 min, remove the dish from the oven and top with the <strong>browned pork steak</strong></p><p>Add any <strong>remaining juices</strong> from the pork to the BBQ glaze</p><p>Brush the pork with the <strong>BBQ glaze </strong>and return the dish to the oven and cook for 13-15 min further or until cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>one pot</strong> <strong>BBQ pork with smoky potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-bbq-pork-with-smoky-potatoes-and-slaw/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot</strong> <strong>BBQ pork with smoky potatoes </strong>and<strong> </strong>the<strong> slaw </strong>to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
